    {
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Reaction.webp",
      "name": "Malice Aforethought",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> Any creature looks directly at the face of the statue.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The creature must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:30] save against the statue's curse.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Stunned]{Stunned 1} as it fights off the curse.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is overcome by an irresistible to urge to climb the ladder in area B35 into the Prison of Woe, where the curse compels the victim to remain in that room. The creature may attempt a Will save at the end of each of its turns. On a success, the curse ends. If another creature activates the statue's curse, the curse immediately ends on the creature it is currently affecting.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the creature may not attempt a new save. The curse can only be broken by magical means or another creature activating the statue's curse.</p>"
        },
